# ============================================================
# 6. CODING CONVENTIONS
# ============================================================

# Python:
#   - Use async def for all FastAPI route handlers and WebSocket handlers
#   - Use run_in_executor for ALL blocking I/O (ChromaDB, Groq)
#   - Type hints on all function signatures
#   - f-strings for string formatting
#   - No bare except — always catch specific exceptions

# JavaScript / React:
#   - Functional components only, no class components
#   - useRef for WebSocket instance and sessionId (not useState — avoids re-renders)
#   - useEffect cleanup: always close WebSocket and clear intervals on unmount
#   - No prop drilling beyond 2 levels — if needed, use React Context
#   - All fetch calls in try/catch with error state handling
#   - Prefer named exports for components

# General:
#   - Never hardcode localhost URLs — use a config constant at the top of the file:
#       const WS_URL = import.meta.env.VITE_WS_URL || 'ws://localhost:8000'
#       const API_URL = import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL || 'http://localhost:8000'
#   - Never commit .env files
#   - Use semantic variable names — no single-letter vars outside loops

# ============================================================
# 7. COMMON BUGS TO AVOID
# ============================================================

# ⚠️  awaitingClarification must be reset to false after "done" is received
#     following a synthesis loop — easy to forget, breaks subsequent messages.

# ⚠️  confidence message arrives BEFORE the first token — store it in a ref,
#     attach to the message object only when "done" is received.

# ⚠️  KBPanel should PREPEND newEntry immediately (from prop) and not wait
#     for the 5-second polling interval to reflect the new entry.

# ⚠️  ChromaDB cosine distance is in [0, 2] — NOT [0, 1].
#     Always apply: similarity = 1 - (distance / 2)
#     Do NOT use raw distance values for threshold comparisons.

# ⚠️  WebSocket message handler: always parse JSON in try/catch.
#     Malformed messages from the server should not crash the UI.

# ⚠️  seed_if_empty() checks count == 0. If you wipe and re-seed manually,
#     delete the ./chroma_db directory entirely first.

